Description: Fragment of shoulder or lower wall of East Greek pottery closed vase, amphora or oenochoe; interior reserved; exterior slipped white; (if from the lower wall) glaze band above two lines and part of a thin ray. Inscriptions in added white and graffito on exterior.
Curator's comments: Marked in pencil 'A924' and '36' crossed out; 'list 32' on label. The orientation should be with the dipinto reading the right way up.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.760)
